{"lemma":"فَتْقِ","slug":"فَتْقِ","root":"ف.ت.ق","root_slug":"ف-ت-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ت-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَتْقِ","root":"فتق","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n32929","n32930","n32931"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%92%D9%82%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rip, rent, tear, cleft, crack, fissure, slit, slash"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hernia"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/fatq/","/ftaq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32929","headword_ar":"فَتْقٌ","root":"ftq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataqahu","text_ar":"فَتَقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Used as a simple subst.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rent, slit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-  And hence, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A breach in society."},{"kind":"text","text":"] One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rataqa fatoqahumo","text_ar":"رَتَقَ فَتْقَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He closed up the breach that was between them; he reconciled them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he reformed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"amended, the circumstances subsisting between them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rtq","text_ar":"رتق"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  [Hence also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rupture; a hernia;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain malady; a protrusion in the thin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delicate, and soft part of the belly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a malady in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SifaAq","text_ar":"صِفَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peritonæum"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting in a solution of the integument so that a rent takes place in it, and through this passes a strange body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substance, that was confined within it before the rent; and there is no cure for it, except for that which happens, rarely, to children:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a disease that befalls a man in his intestines, consisting in a disruption of a place between these and his scrotum, in consequence of which a flatus collects between the two testicles and they become enlarged;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which case one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbatohu riyHu Alfatoqi","text_ar":"اَصَابَتْهُ رِيحُ الفَتْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a severing of the fat"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cellular substance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that encloses the testicles:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the “ Ghareebáni, ” it is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataq","text_ar":"فَتَق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) and thus it is said to be by Az, and thus it is expl. by him: (O:) or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rending of the skin between the scrotum and the lower part of the belly, in consequence of which"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"some of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the intestines fall into the scrotum:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) accord. to Ibráheem El-Harbee,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rupture of the bladder."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b5-  [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rent"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the clouds: see 4:] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataqN","text_ar":"فَتَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[likewise] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gap"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the clouds: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwqN","text_ar":"فُتُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b6-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An open, and a spacious, place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place upon which rain has not fallen when it has fallen upon what is around it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataqapN","text_ar":"فَتَقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies thus, applied to a land: pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwqN","text_ar":"فُتُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAmN *uw","text_ar":"عَامٌ ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfutuwqi","text_ar":"الفُتُوقِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A year of little rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, See an ex., from a rájiz, in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zl","text_ar":"زل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b8-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dawn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataqN","text_ar":"فَتَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K, TA:) signifying also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breaking"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of the dawn; as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AunoZuro A_ilaY fataqi Alfajori","text_ar":"اُنْظُرْ اـِلَى فَتَقِ الفَجْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Look thou at the rising,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breaking, of the dawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfatiyqu","text_ar":"الفَتِيقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"likewise signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the dawn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned by El-Isbahánee, and in the B. (TA.) ―         -b9-  See also 4, last sentence but one, for a meaning of the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwqN","text_ar":"فُتُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K","Mgh","O","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n32930","headword_ar":"فَتَقٌ","root":"ftq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatiqat","text_ar":"فَتِقَت"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a woman: ―         -b2-  and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatiqa","text_ar":"فَتِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a year:] as a subst.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatoqN","text_ar":"فَتْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places: ―         -b3-  and see also 7."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n32931","headword_ar":"فُتُقٌ","root":"ftq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a woman, signifies ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutafat~iqapN","text_ar":"مُتَفَتِّقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlkalaAmi","text_ar":"بِالكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Diffuse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profuse, in speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though bursting therewith]: (S, O, K, TA; [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munofatiqap","text_ar":"مُنْفَتِقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loquacious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK:) or, accord. to ISk, so applied,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that mars"},{"kind":"text","text":"(↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tufat~iqu","text_ar":"تُفَتِّقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rends"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TK"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}